cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a technique using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) to determine the gender of children based on hand radiographs. This falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions the use of Class Activation Mapping (CAM) to identify the area of attention in the hand radiographs. CAM is a technique used in information retrieval to highlight important regions in an image. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses machine learning techniques such as CNN to determine the gender of children. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper mentions the application of the proposed technique in forensic or medico-legal investigation as well as in anthropology. These fields involve human-computer interaction in terms of using technology to aid in investigations. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the analysis of hand radiographs, which can be considered as a form of multimedia data.
